  description: "This essential supplement follows on the heels of \\Product[TSR 9516]{Faiths & Avatars}, which detailed the rules by which deities function in the \\Place[Forgotten Realms]{Realms}, and describes more of the religions and powers of the \\Place[Forgotten Realms]{Realms}. Each divine power is overed in depth, and each entry has information about a deity\'s appearance, personality, worshipers, portfolio, aliases, domain name, superior, allies, foes, symbol, worshipers\' alignments, avatar, manifestations, church, and specialty priests. The information on these faiths include their core dogma, day-to-day activities of priests, holy days and important ceremonies, major centers of worship, affiliated orders, and the priestly vestments and adventuring garb of members of the clergy. Finally, each entry contains spells specific to each of the faiths. \\Product[TSR 9563]{Powers & Pantheons} includes: \\list {The demipowers of the \\Place[Faer\\hat{u}n]{Faer\\hat{u}nian} pantheon: \\God{Finder Wyvernspur}, \\God[Savras]{Savras the All-Seeing}, \\God{Sharess}, \\God[Valkur]{Valkur the Mighty}, \\God{Uthgar}, \\God{Ulutiu}, and others.} {The powers of the \\Place[Mulhorand]{Mulhorandi}, \\Place[Chult]{Chultan} and the deceased \\Place[Unther]{Untheric} pantheons.} {Expanded and clarified specialty priest classes for all religions with priesthoods.} {Religion-specific spells for all faiths with priesthoods.} {Color illustrations of priests from every faith in ceremonial dress.} {Five showpiece temples of the \\Place[Forgotten Realms]{Realms} detailed with illustrations, color maps, and extensive descriptions of their locales, inhabitants, and iteriors.} {The three known \\Monster[Elder Elemental Evil]{Elder Elemental Evils} of the \\Place[Forgotten Realms]{Realms} described in \\Product[Monster Compendium]{Monstrous Compendium} appendix form.} Suitable for all levels of play."
}
